    "where t n * represents the total time steps for agent n * to reach the goal.",
    "Figure 7 shows an example of calculating Effective Velocity in given episodes.",
    "Using L(n *) as the numerator term instead of L A * (n *) would result in a constant v eff (= 1 grid∕timestep) in discrete envi- ronments, making it ineffective as a quality indicator.",
    "Using L A * (n *) allows v eff to measure the effective distance traveled within a single time step.",
    "In discrete environments, v eff still aligns with D because agents maintain a constant speed for every time step, resulting in a proportional relationship between the total time step and the traveled distance."
